        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 10:45PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1045 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Lake Isabella to 5 miles northwest of
Stanton. Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Stanton, Edmore, and Lake Isabella around 1050 PM EDT.
Mount Pleasant and Rosebush around 1100 PM EDT.
Shepherd around 1110 PM EDT.
Alma around 1115 PM EDT.
St. Louis around 1120 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include McBride, Westville,
Elm Hall, Cedar Lake, Entrican, Millbrook, Gratiot Community Airport,
Vestaburg, Forest Hill, and Sumner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
